{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A pure unit test of manifest validation can miss a real failure where the loader imports plugin code too early due to wiring/order bugs. Use real plugin folders and entry files with observable side effects to verify rejection happens before any import/execute step.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one invalid plugin (`manifest.json` missing a required field) and an entry module that writes a sentinel file or flips a process-global flag on evaluation. Run the real loader against the directory. Assert: (1) loader reports manifest validation failure, (2) sentinel side effect never occurs, and (3) plugin `onLoad` is never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is dependency-resolution + hook invocation ordering across multiple plugin modules. A mocked unit test of topological sort can miss loader wiring mistakes between resolver output and actual hook execution.","test_description":"Create temp plugins A and B on disk; A manifest depends on B. Each plugin `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory array or temp log file. Run the real loader. Assert recorded order is `[\"B\",\"A\"]` and both were loaded exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection correctness must be validated in the real loader flow: manifest read, graph build, error report, and load suppression. Unit graph tests can miss that the loader still imports or invokes hooks despite detected cycles.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B where A depends on B and B depends on A. Give each entry module and `onLoad` a visible side effect (e.g., append to temp file). Run loader and capture errors. Assert: (1) cycle error is reported with both plugin names, (2) no entry side effects, (3) no `onLoad` side effects for A or B.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.64,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an ordering guarantee between module evaluation and hook call in the real runtime path. Mocking import behavior can hide failures in async/dynamic import sequencing.","test_description":"Create one plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInit = \"executed\"` at top level and exports `onLoad` that asserts this value exists, then records success. Run loader. Assert `onLoad` runs and sees the executed marker; additionally assert no premature `onLoad` call happened before marker creation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure risk is in cross-plugin orchestration and failure isolation. Unit tests of error handling can miss scheduler/loader-state bugs where one throw aborts unrelated plugins.","test_description":"Create plugins: F (throws in `onLoad`), D (depends on F), and U (independent). Run loader. Assert: (1) F error is captured/reported, (2) D is not initialized due to dependency failure, (3) U still initializes successfully, and (4) loader completes with partial-failure status rather than global abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]}
